Male genitalia (
Fig. 17
). Uncus stout, gradually narrowed, strongly sclerotized with apex hooked; a pair of gnathos long, curved; valva broad medially, with a small protuberance near apex, apex truncate; saccus broad and short; aedeagus strongly upcurved medially; vesica with numerous small cornuti spinules.

Female genitalia (
Figs 20, 21
). apophyses posteriores longer than apophyses anteriores, slender with rounded tips; antrum sclerotized, plate-like with posterior part slightly incised and lateral sides expanded; ductus bursae sclerotized and nearly straight; corpus bursae membranous without signum.
